title: More prep tournament results from Monday
text:
Published: Tue, October 20, 2015 @ 12:00 a.m. 
GIRLS SOCCER 
Austintown Fitch 6, Louisville 0 
AUSTINTOWN 
Goals for Fitch (12-4-1) were scored by Jordan Evans (2), Kaelyn Puhalla, Jackie Muccio, Maia Totterdale, and Tiffany Aliberti, with assists from Evans and Totterdale. Fitch outshot Louisville 16-2, and Fitch also dominated corner kicks 6-3. Soriya Rezapourian had one save for Fitch, and Allie Bourne had 10 for Louisville. 
Boardman 10, Canton McKinley 1 
BOARDMAN 
Sarah Downie paced the Spartans with four goals, while Alisa Earvin scored two. Skylar Bryant, Anna Deeley, Cara Higgins and Cassie Stipp also notched a goal apiece, while Stipp had five assists and Higgins had two. In the net, Camille Holzschuh recorded five saves for Boardman. 
Division II 
Poland 8, Girard 1 
POLAND 
Poland was led by Jessica Miller and Maggie Sebest with two goals each. Poland also got single goals from Megan Marsico, Laiken Maurer, Breanna Craig and Rebekah Thomas. Poland had 2 assists from Breanna Stackpole and Marsico and one assist from Miller. Jackie Kenreich scored the only goal for Girard. Poland outshot Girard 16-2. 
Southeast 2, Salem 0 
SALEM 
Erin Fisher scored both goals for Southeast (11-5-1) in the second half, with an assist from Andrea Radcliff. Southeast outshot Salem (8-8-1) 14-10, but both teams had three corner kicks. Elizabeth Angel had nine saves for Southeast. 
Division III 
Newton Falls 4, Our Lady of the Elms 0 
NEWTON FALLS 
Sara Reinhart, Jaymie Cooper, Makenna Willyard, and Tara Bachrams each scored once for Newton, and Caitlyn Conway had four saves. Elmâ€™s goalkeeper, Holcomb, had ten saves. 
Springfield 1, Lake Center Christian 0 
HARTVILLE 
Eighth-seeded Springfield defeated seventh-seeded Lake Center thanks to a goal by Sam Berlin, which was assisted by Anna Ohlin. Lex Silke notched four saves for the Tigers, while Julia Karmie had 10 saves for Lake Center. 
VOLLEYBALL 
Girard 22-25-27-25, Poland 25-23-25-16 
BELOIT 
For Girard (12-11), Sydney Teter had 20 kills and four blocks, Melanie Bakes had 50 assists, Megan Payich had 11 points, Emily Scarnecchia had three aces, and Makayla Trebella had 28 digs. 
Lakeview 25-25-25, Painesville Harvey 5-10-3 
JEFFERSON 
Jensen Silbaugh had 10 kills for the Bulldogs, while Annie Pavlansky notched 16 points, Laney Lytle had 19 assists and Maddie Butch had nine digs. 
Division III 
East Palestine 25-25-25, Campbell 23-12-8 
SALEM 
For East Palestine, Madyson Pickett had 15 points, Jessica Leakehad eight digs, Brystin Trosky had 21 kills, and Marlaina Frye had 17 assists. 
Mineral Ridge 29-25-23-25, Champion 27-15-25-15 
LEAVITTSBURG 
For Champion, Jackie Mulvain had 7 kills, Summer Fassnacht had 3 kills and 9 assists, and Ashley Naylor had 31 digs. 
Division IV 
Southern Local 25-25-25, Valley Christian 14-9-14 
COLUMBIANA 
For Southern Local, Hannah Brothers had 14 points and 24 assists, Anna Sevak had three blocks, Alivia Brothers had 10 digs, and Abby Smalley had 10 kills. For Valley Christian, Marissa Davis had 28 digs. 
Lake Center 25-19-25-25, Sebring 21-25-19-19 
COLUMBIANA 
Murphy Flowers had 22 digs and 12 kills, Sydney Smith had nine points, Lisa Cathey had 21 assists, and Olivia Woods had three aces. 
Wellsville 25-25-25, Lowellville 18-8-11 
COLUMBIANA 
For Wellsville, Kiki Perry had five blocks, Ashley Bennett had 17 kills, Regan Pierson had 34 assists, Emily Russell had nine digs, and Peyton Davidson had 10 points. For Lowellville, Grace Sotlar had one ace and Courtney Conkin had 12 digs and five kills.
